            <li>Male contain 76ml Blood/Kg. 50ml blood is needed for body circulation. Extra 26 ml/Kg remains in the body. Let’s consider a male of 50kg. He contains 50*26= 1300ml extra blood. In case of female they contain 66ml Blood/Kg. Only 50ml blood is needed for body circulation. Extra 16 ml/Kg remains in the body. Let’s consider a female of 50kg. She contains 50*16= 900ml extra blood. But for donation 450 ml blood is required from this extra blood. </li>
            <li>By donating blood, many lives are saved and hope is given to many whose situation may otherwise be hopeless. Blood donors give such patients a second lease of life.</li>
